text:
Jeanne Elizabeth Wilson (February 18, 1926 – April 18, 2018) was an American competition swimmer. She was born in Chicago, Illinois. She represented the United States at the 1948 Summer Olympics in London. She competed in the 200-meter breaststroke, recording a time of 3:18.3.
Wilson died on April 18, 2018 in Lafayette, Indiana at the age of 92.
